---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Statement of Faith - Bibles & Jiu Jitsu"
  description="Explore our core Christian beliefs and biblical foundation. Learn how our faith in God's Word guides our unique approach to combining spiritual growth with physical training through Jiu Jitsu."
>
  <div class="bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-24">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-12 text-center">Statement of Faith</h1>

      <div class="prose prose-lg mx-auto">
        <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg text-center mb-16">
          At Bibles and Jiu Jitsu, our foundation is built upon the unchanging truths of God's Word.
          As we train both body and spirit, we stand firmly on these essential doctrines of the
          Christian faith. We believe these truths shape who we are and guide everything we do in
          our fellowship.
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-12">
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The Bible</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">
              The Bible, and only the Bible, is the authoritative Word of God. It alone is the final
              authority in determining all doctrinal truths. In its original writing, it is
              inspired, infallible, and inerrant.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 italic text-sm">
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=2%20Timothy%203%3A16&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">II Timothy 3:16</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=2%20Peter%201%3A20-21&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">II Peter 1:20-21</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Proverbs%2030%3A5&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Proverbs 30:5</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Romans%2016%3A25-26&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Romans 16:25-26</a
              >
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The Trinity</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">
              There is one God, eternally existent in three persons: Father, Son, and Holy Spirit.
              These three are co-equal and co-eternal.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 italic text-sm">
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=1%20John%205%3A7&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">I John 5:7</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Genesis%201%3A26&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Genesis 1:26</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Matthew%203%3A16-17&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Matthew 3:16-17</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Hebrews%203%3A7-11&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Hebrews 3:7-11</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Isaiah%209%3A6&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Isaiah 9:6</a
              >
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Jesus Christ</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">
              Jesus Christ is God the Son, the second person of the Trinity. On earth, Jesus was
              100% God and 100% man. He is the only man ever to have lived a sinless life. He was
              born of a virgin, lived a sinless life, performed miracles, died on the cross for
              mankind, and atoned for our sins through the shedding of His blood. He rose from the
              dead on the third day according to the Scriptures, ascended to the right hand of the
              Father, and will return again in power and glory.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 italic text-sm">
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=John%201%3A1%2C14%2C20%3A28&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">John 1:1, 14, 20:28</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=1%20Timothy%203%3A16&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">I Timothy 3:16</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Isaiah%209%3A6&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Isaiah 9:6</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Philippians%202%3A5-6&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Philippians 2:5-6</a
              >
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Salvation</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">
              We are saved by grace through faith in Jesus Christ; His death, burial, and
              resurrection. Salvation is a gift from God, not a result of our good works or of any
              human efforts.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 italic text-sm">
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Ephesians%202%3A8-9&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Ephesians 2:8-9</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Galatians%202%3A16%2C3%3A8&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Galatians 2:16, 3:8</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Titus%203%3A5&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Titus 3:5</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Romans%2010%3A9-10&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Romans 10:9-10</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Acts%2016%3A31&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Acts 16:31</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Hebrews%209%3A22&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Hebrews 9:22</a
              >
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Repentance</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">
              Repentance is the commitment to turn away from sin in every area of our lives and to
              follow Christ, which allows us to receive His redemption and to be regenerated by the
              Holy Spirit. Thus, through repentance, we receive forgiveness of sins and appropriate
              salvation.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 italic text-sm">
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Acts%202%3A21%2C3%3A19&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Acts 2:21, 3:19</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=1%20John%201%3A9&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">I John 1:9</a
              >
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Baptism of the Holy Spirit</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">
              Given at Pentecost, it is the promise of the Father, sent by Jesus after His
              Ascension, to empower the Church to preach the Gospel throughout the whole earth.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 italic text-sm">
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Joel%202%3A28-29&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Joel 2:28-29</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Matthew%203%3A11&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Matthew 3:11</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Mark%2016%3A17&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Mark 16:17</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Acts%201%3A5%2C2%3A1-4%2C17%2C38-39%2C8%3A14-17%2C10%3A38%2C44-47&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Acts 1:5, 2:1-4; 17, 38-39, 8:14-17, 10:38, 44-47</a
              >
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Gifts of the Holy Spirit</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">
              The Holy Spirit is manifested through a variety of spiritual gifts to build and
              sanctify the church, demonstrate the validity of the resurrection, and confirm the
              power of the Gospel. The Bible list of these gifts are not necessarily exhaustive, and
              the gifts may occur in various combinations. All believers are commanded to earnestly
              desire the manifestation of the gifts in their lives. These gifts always operate in
              harmony with the Scriptures and should never be used in violation of Biblical
              parameters.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 italic text-sm">
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Hebrews%202%3A4&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Hebrews 2:4</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Ephesians%204%3A16&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Ephesians 4:16</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=1%20Timothy%204%3A14&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">I Timothy 4:14</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=2%20Timothy%201%3A6-7&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">II Timothy 1:6-7</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=1%20Corinthians%2012%3A1-31%2C14%3A1-40&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">I Corinthians 12:1-31, 14:1-40</a
              >
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The Church</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">
              The church is the Body of Christ, the habitation of God through the Spirit, with
              divine appointments for the fulfillment of Jesus' Great Commission. Every person who
              is born of the Spirit is an integral part of the church as a member of the body of
              believers. There is a spiritual unity of all believers in our Lord Jesus Christ.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 italic text-sm">
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Ephesians%201%3A22%2C2%3A19-22&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Ephesians 1:22; 2:19-22</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Hebrews%2012%3A23&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Hebrews 12:23</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=John%2017%3A11%2C20-23&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">John 17:11, 20-23</a
              >
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Water Baptism</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">
              Following faith in the Lord Jesus Christ, the new convert is commanded by the Word of
              God to be baptized in water in the Name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy
              Spirit.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 italic text-sm">
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Matthew%2028%3A19&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Matthew 28:19</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Acts%202%3A38&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Acts 2:38</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Mark%2016%3A16&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Mark 16:16</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Acts%208%3A12%2C36-38%2C10%3A47-48&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Acts 8:12, 36-38; 10:47-48</a
              >
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Communion</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">
              A unique time of communion in the presence of God when the elements of bread and grape
              juice (the Body and Blood of the Lord Jesus Christ) are taken in remembrance of Jesus'
              sacrifice on the Cross.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 italic text-sm">
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Matthew%2026%3A26-29&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Matthew 26:26-29</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=1%20Corinthians%2010%3A16&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">1 Corinthians 10:16</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=1%20Corinthians%2011%3A23-25&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">1 Corinthians 11:23-25</a
              >
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The Resurrection</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">
              Jesus Christ was physically resurrected from the dead in a glorified body three days
              after His death on the cross. Both the saved and the lost will be resurrected; they
              that are saved to the resurrection of life, and they that are lost to the resurrection
              of eternal damnation.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 italic text-sm">
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Luke%2024%3A16&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Luke 24:16</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=John%202%3A19-21%2C20%3A26-28&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">John 2:19-21, 20:26-28</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Acts%2024%3A15&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Acts 24:15</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Philippians%201%3A21-23%2C3%3A21&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Philippians 1:21-23, 3:21</a
              >
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The Second Coming</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">
              Jesus Christ will physically and visibly return to earth for the second time to
              establish His Kingdom. This will occur at a date undisclosed by the Scriptures.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 italic text-sm">
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Matthew%2024%3A30%2C26%3A63-64&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Matthew 24:30, 26:63-64</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Acts%201%3A9-11&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Acts 1:9-11</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=1%20Thessalonians%204%3A15-17&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">I Thessalonians 4:15-17</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=2%20Thessalonians%201%3A7-8&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">II Thessalonians 1:7-8</a
              >;{' '}
              <a
                href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Revelation%201%3A7&version=NIV"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="hover:text-blue-600">Revelation 1:7</a
              >
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
